{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a specific offence and sentence for Murder, Desecration & Concealment ",
        "additional_details": "This could be known as \"Chantel's Law\".\r\n\r\nAt present there is not a specific, standalone offence of Murder, Desecration and Concealment. Killers are given all different sentences for crimes involving these actions. There should be a consistent sentence for Murder, Desecration and Concealment. Too often the victims remains are not found. \r\n \r\nThis would send a clear message out.",
        "background": "Judges currently use their discretion when sentencing in cases involving murder, desecration and concealment. We want there to be a new standalone offence of Murder, Desecration and Concealment, with its own mandatory minimum custodial sentence.",
        "closed_at": null,
